node.title: Search for William Tyrrell's remains to end this week
node.description: The "painstaking" four-week search for William Tyrrell's remains will end "in coming days", police say. The efforts were sparked by "new information", but have so far turned up nothing of note.
node.content:
["The search for William Tyrrell's remains will end \"in coming days\", police say.", "Officers and volunteers have been scouring several locations in and around the town of Kendall,\u00a0on the NSW Mid-North Coast, where the missing boy was last seen in 2014.", "The operation has been underway for four weeks.", "According to\u00a0Detective Chief Superintendent Darren Bennett, the search was sparked by \"new information\".", "There have been more than 1,000 persons of interest in the case, which has puzzled police for years.", "William was last seen while playing out the front of his foster grandmother's home.", "In an update two weeks ago, Detective Chief Superintendent Bennett described the search as \"painstaking\".\u00a0", "He said officers were \"happy with the progress\" but that there was \"no great milestone to report\".", "Wet weather has caused delays to the search.", "", "
Police divers have found nothing after joining the search last month.(ABC News: Mark Reddie)
", "While several items have been removed from the search site for forensic analysis, the ABC understands that none is\u00a0expected to provide information that cracks the case.", "Before the search began, police confirmed publicly for the first time they were looking for William's remains.", "Over the past four weeks, several forensic experts have attended a site, about 900 metres from the home formerly owned by William's late foster grandmother.\u00a0", "It's been the main site for the most recent search efforts.", "Officers have also drained a creek and water tanks in the area, while police divers scoured a nearby dam.", "Police also seized the foster grandmother's\u00a0car from its new owner. It\u00a0is being examined.", "A coronial inquest into William's death is ongoing.", "In a statement, a police spokesperson said Deputy State Coroner Harriet Grahame had been kept up to date with developments from the search.", "\"Investigators would like to thank the NSW Rural Fire Service, Salvation Army\u00a0and the local community for their hospitality and assistance,\" the spokesperson\u00a0said.", "They said officers remained \"committed to finding William Tyrrell\"."]
